# Plan Design Review

Use this skill when an approved spec and current draft plan declare material UI changes or `Design Review Required: yes` in `Risk & Gate Signals`.

This is a planning-time design gate. It happens before implementation and before the plan becomes `Engineering Approved`.

## Scope

Review the exact plan artifact under `docs/featureforge/plans/`.

- focus on material UI changes
- check information architecture, interaction flows, loading / empty / error states, responsive behavior, accessibility expectations, and design-system alignment
- keep the review bounded to design fidelity and implementation readiness
- do not approve engineering execution here

## Artifact Contract

Write a runtime-owned design review artifact under `$_SP_STATE_DIR/projects/$SLUG/` for the exact plan revision.

Use a branch-scoped runtime filename that matches `*-plan-design-review-<timestamp>.md` so workflow routing can discover the current branch artifact deterministically.

The artifact must include:

- `# Plan Design Review Result`
- `Artifact Kind: plan-design-review`
- `Schema Version: 1`
- `Artifact Provenance: runtime-owned`
- `Retention Policy: featureforge:authoritative-runtime-artifact`
- `Source Plan`
- `Source Plan Revision`
- `Source Plan Fingerprint`
- `Branch`
- `Repo`
- `Receipt Fingerprint`
- `Result: pass | revise`
- `Generated By: featureforge:plan-design-review`
- `Generated At`
- explicit findings for state coverage, interaction risks, and required plan changes

## Required Outcome

- If design review fails or needs changes, return control to `featureforge:writing-plans`.
- If design review passes, return the same draft plan to `featureforge:plan-eng-review` for final engineering approval.

Use `skills/plan-design-review/references/checklist.md` as the minimum review floor.